  <sec sec-type="methods" id="SEC2">
    <title>METHODS AND IMPLEMENTATION</title>
    <sec id="SEC2-1">
      <title>EpiAlignment algorithm</title>
      <p>The EpiAlignment algorithm aims to identify the optimal alignment between two genomic regions, denoted by <italic>A</italic> and <italic>B</italic>, with information from both the genome and the epigenome. Each genomic region contains two types of data, namely the DNA sequence and the epigenomic profile, denoted by <inline-formula><tex-math id="M1">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
